"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872322","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-29","<p>The Cold Weather Payment scheme is administered at weather station level rather than any other standard GB geography such as constituency level. The coverage area for each weather station is determined by the Met Office which assesses the most appropriate weather station for each postcode area. Cold Weather Payments are triggered when the average temperature recorded at the weather station has been recorded as, or is forecast to be, 0<sup>o</sup>C or below over seven consecutive days.</p><p> </p><p>The estimated numbers of Cold Weather Payments are produced at a weather station level and cannot be broken down further. As a result, the estimate given below is subject to a margin of error when matching to the Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath constituency.</p><p> </p><p>The postcode areas within Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath constituency are covered by the Edinburgh Gogarbank, Leuchars, and Strathallan weather stations. Since 1<sup>st</sup> January 2018, an estimated 86,000 eligible recipients in coverage of these weather stations have received at least one Cold Weather Payment. Not all of these eligible recipients will live within the Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath constituency.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872322/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-29T11:44:39.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872322/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872322/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-26","Cold Weather Payments: Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what information her Department holds on the number of people in Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath constituency who have been eligible for cold weather payments since the beginning of 2018.","false","Biography information for Lesley Laird","Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath","Lesley Laird","134236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872323","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-29","<p>You do not need to apply for a Cold Weather Payment, if you are eligible you will usually be paid automatically. Therefore, my Department doesn’t hold any information on the number of people in Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath constituency who have applied for a cold weather payment.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872323/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-29T10:52:34.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872323/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872323/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-26","Cold Weather Payments: Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what information her Department holds on the number of people in Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath constituency who have applied for cold weather payments in 2018.","false","Biography information for Lesley Laird","Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath","Lesley Laird","134237"
