"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872453","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-09","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office has not identified any occasions where British High Commissions or Embassies put potential clients in touch with representatives of those companies.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872453/answer",,,,,,"2018-04-09T13:38:27.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872453/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872453/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-26","Embassies: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government on how many occasions have any British High Commissions or Embassies put potential clients in touch with representatives of SCL Elections or Cambridge Analytica.","false","Biography information for Lord Hain",,"Lord Hain","HL6636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872454","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-29","<p>Neither the Department nor its arm’s length bodies hold this information.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872454/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-29T10:59:17.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872454/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872454/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-26","NHS: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people working in the NHS are employed by third party companies in (a) Camberwell and Peckham constituency and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","134350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872455","Home Office","false","2018-04-05","<p>Since 2010 the Home Office has revoked over 900 Tier 4 Licences which will include circumstances where the sponsor was found to be non-compliant with our requirements. The Home Office does not routinely hold data on the activities of or changes made to an institution after it has been revoked, as we no longer retain any oversight of the institution.</p><p> </p><p>When new Tier 4 licence applications are made, we undertake checks on an institution to see if they have previously had a licence revoked. We will also check any key personnel and others involved in the running of the institution to examine their suitability to hold a sponsor licence. This will include checks regarding any previous ownership of revoked institutions and the circumstances for revocation. Where appropriate we will refuse a licence application where we are not satisfied the institution or personnel involved meet the suitability criteria to hold a Tier 4 sponsor licence.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872455/answer",,,,,,"2018-04-05T13:11:28.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872455/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872455/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-26","Visas: Fraud","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what estimate they have made of the number of bogus colleges previously closed down for having sponsored visas for people who intended to work in the UK rather than study that are now operating under new names.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hamwee",,"Baroness Hamwee","HL6637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872456","Department for Education","false","2018-04-06","<p>EU students, staff and researchers make an important contribution to our universities. We want that contribution to continue and are confident – given the quality of our higher education sector – that it will.</p><p> </p><p>Applications for courses starting in 2019/20 do not open until September 2018, and we will ensure students starting courses in that academic year have information well in advance of this date.</p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872456/answer",,,,,,"2018-04-06T12:43:53.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872456/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872456/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-26","Overseas Students: EU Nationals","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether student loans will be available for EU students studying in the UK during the (1) 2019–20, and (2) 2020–21, academic years.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL6638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872457","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-29","<p>Information on the average waiting time for general practitioner appointments at local and national level is not collected or held centrally.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872457/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-29T10:36:43.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872457/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872457/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-26","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what the average waiting time for a GP appointment was in (a) the London Borough of Southwark; (b) London and (c) England, in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","134351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872458","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-09","<p>The responsibility for oral health improvement and the power to make proposals in relation to water fluoridation rests with local authorities and Public Health England (PHE) has not been asked to make an independent assessment of the potential oral health impact of any proposal from Bedford Borough Council.</p><p>Bedford Borough Council has made a formal proposal to vary water fluoridation arrangements but the Secretary of State has not yet been asked for an opinion on whether the arrangements as varied would be operable and efficient, nor has a view of the water undertaker on this matter or any practical aspects to giving effect to such variation been supplied.</p><p>PHE published a water fluoridation toolkit, <em>Improving oral health: a community water fluoridation toolkit for local authorities,</em> in 2016 to support local authorities and PHE’s national and local leads have provided advice to Bedford Borough Council on the evidence base and processes required by legislation should they wish to proceed with a proposal to vary or terminate water fluoridation arrangements. This includes advising them of the requirement to ensure appropriate consultation is undertaken and directing them to the relevant Act and regulations before any proposals for termination. A copy of <em>Improving oral health: a community water fluoridation toolkit for local authorities</em> is attached.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872458/answer","Fluoridation_Toolkit_-_Publications_gateway_version_20160304.pdf","Fluoridation_Toolkit_-_Publications_gateway_version_20160304.pdf","Fluoridation Toolkit","Fluoridation Toolkit","HL6640 ; HL6641 ; HL6642 ; HL6643","2018-04-09T15:04:13.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872458/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872458/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-26","Fluoride: Drinking Water","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what discussions they have had with Bedford Borough Council concerning the obligation to ensure that any proposal to terminate water fluoridation schemes is only determined after appropriate consultation, as set out in the Water Industry Act 1991.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL6639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872459","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-09","<p>The responsibility for oral health improvement and the power to make proposals in relation to water fluoridation rests with local authorities and Public Health England (PHE) has not been asked to make an independent assessment of the potential oral health impact of any proposal from Bedford Borough Council.</p><p>Bedford Borough Council has made a formal proposal to vary water fluoridation arrangements but the Secretary of State has not yet been asked for an opinion on whether the arrangements as varied would be operable and efficient, nor has a view of the water undertaker on this matter or any practical aspects to giving effect to such variation been supplied.</p><p>PHE published a water fluoridation toolkit, <em>Improving oral health: a community water fluoridation toolkit for local authorities,</em> in 2016 to support local authorities and PHE’s national and local leads have provided advice to Bedford Borough Council on the evidence base and processes required by legislation should they wish to proceed with a proposal to vary or terminate water fluoridation arrangements. This includes advising them of the requirement to ensure appropriate consultation is undertaken and directing them to the relevant Act and regulations before any proposals for termination. A copy of <em>Improving oral health: a community water fluoridation toolkit for local authorities</em> is attached.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872459/answer","Fluoridation_Toolkit_-_Publications_gateway_version_20160304.pdf","Fluoridation_Toolkit_-_Publications_gateway_version_20160304.pdf","Fluoridation Toolkit","Fluoridation Toolkit","HL6639 ; HL6641 ; HL6642 ; HL6643","2018-04-09T15:04:13.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872459/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872459/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-26","Fluoride: Drinking Water","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether Bedford Borough Council has consulted (1) the Secretary of State, and (2) the water undertaker, on whether that Council's proposal to terminate the water fluoridation scheme in Bedford can be deemed operable and efficient.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL6640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872460","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-29","<p>NHS England has a legal duty to commission National Health Service primary care dental services to meet local needs. NHS England is responsible for ensuring that NHS primary dental services are accessible, and that they contribute to the prevention of dental disease, in addition to its treatment.</p><p> </p><p>Access nationally remains high. 22.1 million adults saw an NHS dentist in the 24 months ending in 31 December 2017 and 6.9 million children in the 12 months ending in 31 December 2017. However, there are areas where there is further to go to ensure that all those who want to access NHS dental care can do so.</p><p> </p><p>New ways of providing primary care dental services are being tested by the Department and NHS England which aims to further improve oral health and increase access to NHS dental services, by preventing as well as treating disease. Alongside this, is NHS England’s Starting Well programme, which aims to improve access to dental services for children known to be at greater risk of dental disease and who are not currently being seen by a dentist.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872460/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-29T10:40:10.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872460/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872460/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-26","Dental Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans he has to improve access to NHS dentistry services.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","134352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872461","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-09","<p>The responsibility for oral health improvement and the power to make proposals in relation to water fluoridation rests with local authorities and Public Health England (PHE) has not been asked to make an independent assessment of the potential oral health impact of any proposal from Bedford Borough Council.</p><p>Bedford Borough Council has made a formal proposal to vary water fluoridation arrangements but the Secretary of State has not yet been asked for an opinion on whether the arrangements as varied would be operable and efficient, nor has a view of the water undertaker on this matter or any practical aspects to giving effect to such variation been supplied.</p><p>PHE published a water fluoridation toolkit, <em>Improving oral health: a community water fluoridation toolkit for local authorities,</em> in 2016 to support local authorities and PHE’s national and local leads have provided advice to Bedford Borough Council on the evidence base and processes required by legislation should they wish to proceed with a proposal to vary or terminate water fluoridation arrangements. This includes advising them of the requirement to ensure appropriate consultation is undertaken and directing them to the relevant Act and regulations before any proposals for termination. A copy of <em>Improving oral health: a community water fluoridation toolkit for local authorities</em> is attached.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872461/answer","Fluoridation_Toolkit_-_Publications_gateway_version_20160304.pdf","Fluoridation_Toolkit_-_Publications_gateway_version_20160304.pdf","Fluoridation Toolkit","Fluoridation Toolkit","HL6639 ; HL6640 ; HL6642 ; HL6643","2018-04-09T15:04:13.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872461/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/872461/answer",,,,,"17","Health and