be publishing ‘Commissioning better oral health for vulnerable older people’ to support commissioning of health and social care services that will have positive impacts on the oral health of vulnerable older people.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/870259/answer",,,,,"134122","2018-03-28T15:00:53.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/870259/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/870259/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-23","Dental Services: Care Homes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that all care home residents receive an oral health assessment.","false","Biography information for Emma Hardy","Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle","Emma Hardy","134123"
