"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869397","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-27","<p>The Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union has not met with representatives of SCL Group or Cambridge Analytica.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Departments publish quarterly details of Ministers’ meetings with external organisations on GOV.UK. These can be found at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=transparency-data&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-exiting-the-european-union&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=transparency-data&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-exiting-the-european-union&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>As well as ministerial meetings, departmental officials meet external organisations on a regular and ongoing basis.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869397/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T12:01:17.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869397/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869397/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-03-22","Department for Exiting the European Union: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he has met represenatives of (a) SCL Group and (b) Cambridge Analytica.","false","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","133911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869398","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-27","<p>DWP do not hold information regarding the numbers of asylum seekers who have been granted indefinite leave to remain in the UK. However, when the Home Office grant the application for indefinite leave they forward the personal details to NINo operations and a NINo is allocated within 48 hours.</p><p> </p><p>From 15 January 2018 this process is applicable to the principle family member and any adult dependants aged 16 or over in the refugees family. With the NINo being allocated within 48 hours this facilitates the smooth transition from asylum support to mainstream benefits.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869398/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T10:46:59.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869398/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869398/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-22","Immigration: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people who have indefinite leave to remain and have reached the end of their eligibility for asylum support are waiting to receive a national insurance number in the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","133912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869399","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-27","<p>The assessment for Personal Independence Payment (PIP) is not designed to capture someone’s condition. Instead it is designed to assess how a claimant’s condition affects their functional ability. The Department therefore encourages claimants to provide as much relevant evidence as necessary to support their claim. The Certificate of Visual Impairment forms part of this suite of evidence but on its own does not provide sufficient information for a comprehensive assessment of functional ability.</p><p>Further information on the assessment process and sources of evidence can be found in Part 1 of the PIP Assessment Guide: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/personal-independence-payment-assessment-guide-for-assessment-providers" target="_blank">Personal Independence Payment (PIP) assessment guide for assessment providers - GOV.UK</a></p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869399/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T10:58:29.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869399/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869399/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-22","Personal Independence Payment: Visual Impairment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions if she will take steps to ensure that claimants need not undergo personal independent payment assessments when they have a Certificate of Visual Impairment.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","133913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869400","Department for Education","false","2018-03-27","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 26 March 2018 to 133602 and 133603 available at: <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=133602" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=133602</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869400/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T16:58:29.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869400/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869400/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-22","Schools: Asbestos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of the removal of asbestos from the school estate in (a) the West Midlands and (b) Coventry.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","133914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869401","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-27","<p>Public Health England (PHE) is aware, through its Mapping of Weight Management Services in 2015, that the majority of local councils in the West Midlands provided weight management services for children, young people and adults. PHE has developed tools to support data collection for the purpose of locally evaluating services, though there are no current plans to evaluate the provision of weight management services in specific regions.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869401/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T11:53:49.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869401/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869401/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-22","Obesity: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department plans to evaluate the provision of weight management services for (a) children and young people and (b) adults in the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","133915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869402","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-27","While the Foreign Secretary has not recently discussed this specific issue with his Israeli counterpart, our Embassy in Tel Aviv and our Consulate-General in Jerusalem frequently urge both the Israeli and Palestinian authorities to take steps to improve conditions in Gaza. Every Israeli and Palestinian has the right to live in peace and security. We strongly condemn the recent attempted assassination of Prime Minister Hamdallah on 13 March, for which there is no justification. The UK continues to support the return of the legitimate Palestinian Authority to Gaza. We urge non-violence, dialogue and progress towards a sustainable Hamas-Fatah reconciliation and an improvement in the humanitarian situation in Gaza.","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869402/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T17:16:05.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869402/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869402/answer","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869402/answer/previousversion/50223","Biography information for Alistair Burt","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-22","Gaza: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his Israeli counterpart on the security situation in Gaza.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","133916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869403","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-27","<p>This information is not available in the format requested.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869403/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T16:09:34.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869403/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869403/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-22","Mental Health Services: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many in-patient mental health beds have been available to patients in (a) the West Midlands and (b) Coventry in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","133917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869404","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-27","<p>Information on the funding of addiction services in the West Midlands is not held centrally. The figures on local authority alcohol and drug treatment actual spend are published annually and available online at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869404/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T16:16:13.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869404/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869404/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-22","Addictions: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much funding has been allocated from the public purse to addiction services in the West Midlands in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","133918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869405","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-27","<p>The public consultation on the draft Animal Welfare (Sentencing and Recognition of Sentience) Bill closed on 31 January 2018. We are currently considering the 9000 responses received to the consultation and will be responding shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869405/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T11:18:09.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869405/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869405/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-22","Animal Welfare (Sentencing and Recognition of Sentience) Bill (Draft)","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he plans to introduce the Animal Welfare (Sentencing and Recognition of Sentience) Bill.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","133919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869406","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-03","<p>The proposals set out in the Housing White Paper underline our commitment to do more to provide the homes we need for all in our society, including new retirement homes. The Government is strengthening national planning policy so that local planning authorities are expected to have clear policies for addressing the housing needs of older people. We will be publishing further guidance on housing for older people this summer.</p><p>In addition, the Housing, Communities and Local Government Select Committee’s report into Housing for Older People has made wide-ranging recommendations to improve this housing provision, to which the Government is currently preparing its response.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869406/answer",,,,,,"2018-04-03T13:30:43.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869406/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869406/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-22","Housing: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to increase the supply of retirement housing, and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Damian Green","Ashford","Damian Green","133920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869407","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-28","<p>Future planning for the civilian support jobs based in York are still in progress and the Department will work with the local Authority and the Government Property Agency to explore potential opportunities to keep civilian posts within the local area.</p><p>Civilian personnel will be managed in accordance with normal Departmental Policy and processes and formal Trades Union consultation will occur in advance of any site closure.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869407/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-28T16:30:01.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869407/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869407/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-22","Military Bases: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to retain civilian support jobs in York following the planned closure of Queen Elizabeth Barracks and Imphal Barracks.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","133921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869408","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-29","<p>The Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) is the United Kingdom Agency responsible for the regulation of medicines used in the UK.</p><p> </p><p>The MHRA has not received any marketing authorisation (licence) applications for a medicinal product that contains raw cannabis, for the treatment of any condition in the UK.</p><p> </p><p>If a licence application for a medicinal product containing raw cannabis is received, the MHRA would assess the data submitted to ensure that the product is safe, has efficacy in the purpose claimed for it, is manufactured to the necessary quality standards and that there is a positive balance of benefits over any risks before approval of the licence.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869408/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-29T11:18:22.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869408/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869408/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-22","Cannabis: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he plans to grant licences for medicinal cannabis products; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tonia Antoniazzi","Gower","Tonia Antoniazzi","133922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869409","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-27","<p>My Department does not make projections for the number of specific types of homes, including retirement homes, which are expected to be built over the next five years.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869409/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T15:59:02.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869409/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869409/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-22","Housing: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what projection his Department has made of the number of retirement homes which will be built between March 2018 and March 2022.","false","Biography information for Damian Green","Ashford","Damian Green","133923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869410","Home Office","false","2018-03-27","<p>Immigration Enforcement work in partnership law enforcement agencies and NGOs in responding to modern slavery and human trafficking offences</p><p>There are 1240 frontline officers within the crime and financial investigations teams (CFI) and immigration, compliance and enforcement teams of Immigration Enforcement, all of whom are trained to identify the indicators of modern slavery and human trafficking.</p><p>Immigration Enforcement are putting in place modern slavery champions across frontline enforcement who will receive enhanced training in this area.</p><p>CFI officers receive a number of Modern Slavery training products including e-learning through the National Centre for Applied Learning Technologies (NCALT) (from the College of Policing) and HO products through Discover.</p><p>They receive a half day first response face to face delivery in their induction programme and a further face to face delivery around the National Referral Mechanism and indicators within Professionalising Investigation Programme ( PIP1) classroom.</p><p>They study further for the national investigators examination ( NIE) and are questioned on Modern Slavery Act offences in the exam. On PIP2 they undertake a full week covering the College Public Protection Learning Programme covering the 13 strands of Public Protection but IE also focus heavily on Modern Slavery. Further to this the Hydra exercise in week 4 is based on a Modern Slavery scenario.</p><p>All modern slavery operations conducted by CFI are debriefed fully. Any issues identified are dealt with and fed into the assurance and training teams.</p><p>CFI has a business assurance framework which provides a formal structure to assurance activity to ensure we adopt a consistent approach across all areas of operations.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869410/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T12:26:54.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869410/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869410/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-22","Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment her Department has made of the adequacy of the number of Immigration Enforcement Officers on preventing human trafficking.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","133924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869411","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-27","<p>Departments publish quarterly details of Ministers’ meetings with external organisations on GOV.UK. These can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministerial-gifts-hospitality-overseas-travel-and-meetings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministerial-gifts-hospitality-overseas-travel-and-meetings</a></p><p> </p><p>As well as ministerial meetings, Departmental officials meet external organisations on a regular and ongoing basis.</p><p> </p><p>Neither the Department nor its Executive Agencies have entered into any contracts with the SCL group or Cambridge Analytica.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869411/answer",,,,,"133926","2018-03-27T11:45:20.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869411/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869411/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-22","Department of Health and Social Care: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he has met with representatives of the SCL group or Cambridge Analytica; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","133925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869412","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-27","<p>Departments publish quarterly details of Ministers’ meetings with external organisations on GOV.UK. These can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministerial-gifts-hospitality-overseas-travel-and-meetings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministerial-gifts-hospitality-overseas-travel-and-meetings</a></p><p> </p><p>As well as ministerial meetings, Departmental officials meet external organisations on a regular and ongoing basis.</p><p> </p><p>Neither the Department nor its Executive Agencies have entered into any contracts with the SCL group or Cambridge Analytica.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869412/answer",,,,,"133925","2018-03-27T11:45:20.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869412/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869412/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-22","Department of Health and Social Care: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department or its agencies has entered into contracts with SCL group or Cambridge Analytica.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","133926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869413","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-27","<p>​The Foreign Secretary and I met Alexander Nix, then CEO of Cambridge Analytica, in December 2016, to better understand the 2016 US presidential election, the political environment that followed and to build relationships with the Trump Presidential campaign. This outreach was part of normal diplomatic business.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869413/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T15:23:00.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869413/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869413/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-22","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Cambridge Analytica​ and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has met with representatives of the SCL group or Cambridge Analytica; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","133927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869414","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-29","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) and its agencies have not entered into any contracts with SCL group since 2009. The FCO held one contract with SCL group in 2008-2009.​</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869414/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-29T09:52:36.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869414/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869414/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-22","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department or its agencies has entered into contracts with SCL group.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","133928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869415","Department for Education","false","2018-04-03","<p>My right hon. Friend, the Secretary of State has not met with representatives of the Strategic Communication Laboratories group or Cambridge Analytica.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869415/answer",,,,,,"2018-04-03T13:02:26.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869415/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869415/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-22","Department for Education: Cambridge Analytica and SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether he has met with representatives of the SCL group or Cambridge Analytica; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","133929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869416","Department for Education","false","2018-04-03","<p>The department have not entered into any commercial contracts with Cambridge Analytica or its parent organisation Strategic Communication Laboratories Group.</p><p> </p><p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: <a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive</a>. Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: <a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a>.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869416/answer",,,,,"133785 ; 133999","2018-04-03T10:51:19.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869416/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869416/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-22","Department for Education: SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether his Department or its agencies has entered into contracts with SCL group.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","133930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869417","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-27","<p>The Department has not entered into any commercial contract with Strategic Communication Laboratories (SCL Group). The Department has no agencies.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869417/answer",,,,,"134000","2018-03-27T11:56:33.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869417/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869417/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-03-22","Department for Exiting the European Union: SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether his Department or its agencies has entered into contracts with SCL group.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","133931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869418","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-29","<p>Number 11 Downing Street is a part of the Cabinet Office estate which is managed as a whole. Separating these costs would not be possible without incurring disproportionate cost.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869418/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-29T09:12:17.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869418/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869418/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-22","11 Downing Street: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much has been spent from the public purse on repairs and maintenance at No. 11 Downing Street in each of the last ten years.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","133932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869419","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-29","<p>Number 10 Downing Street is a part of the Cabinet Office estate which is managed as a whole. Separating these costs would not be possible without incurring disproportionate cost.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869419/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-29T09:09:53.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869419/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869419/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-22","10 Downing Street: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much has been spent from the public purse on repairs and maintenance at No. 10 Downing Street in each of the last ten years.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","133933"
