"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869489","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-28","<p>From our records, the Ministry of Justice (MoJ) and its agencies has not entered into contracts with Strategic Communication Laboratories in each year since 2010.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869489/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-28T14:35:32.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869489/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869489/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-22","Ministry of Justice: SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether (a) his Department and (b) any of his Department's agencies entered into contracts with Strategic Communication Laboratories in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869490","Scotland Office","false","2018-03-28","<p>The Scotland Office and its arm’s length body, the Boundary Commission for Scotland, have not entered into any contracts with Strategic Communication Laboratories.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869490/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-28T11:25:22.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869490/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869490/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-03-22","Scotland Office: SCL Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether (a) his Department and (b) any of his Department's agencies entered into contracts with Strategic Communication Laboratories in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869491","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-27","<p>​The Government remains firmly opposed to the illegal hunting of wildlife, and supports the European Commission's efforts to ensure Member State compliance with EU Directive 2009/147/EC on the Conservation of Wild Birds. Our High Commission in Malta continues to monitor the situation.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869491/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-27T15:19:02.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869491/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/869491/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-22","Malta: Nature Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to his counterpart in Malta on ensuring that the Maltese Government complies with its international obligations on the protection of birds.","false","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Theresa Villiers","134005"
